  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Proverbs 15:20-21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 15:20-21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A wise son, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — See the note on chap. 10:1, where we have the same proverb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Folly is joy to him that is destitute of wisdom —",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He not only works wickedness, but takes pleasure in doing it; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but a man of understanding walketh uprightly ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "יישׁר לכת",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "directeth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "maketh straight, his going; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, ordereth all his actions by the rule of God’s word, and delights in so doing, as may be understood from the opposite clause.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
