  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This collection of Solomonic proverbs began, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 10:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with a proverb having reference to the observance of the fourth commandment,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(Note: The fifth commandment of the Westminster Shorter Catechism is named as the fourth in Luther's catechism.)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and a second chief section, Proverbs 13:1, began in the same way. Here a proverb of the same kind designates the beginning of a third chief section. That the editor was aware of this is shown by the homogeneity of the proverbs, Proverbs 15:19; Proverbs 12:28, which form the conclusion of the first and second sections. We place together first in this new section, Proverbs 15:20-23, in which (with the exception of Proverbs 15:25) the ישׂמח [maketh glad] of the first (Proverbs 10:1) is continued.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and a second chief section, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 13:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", began in the same way. Here a proverb of the same kind designates the beginning of a third chief section. That the editor was aware of this is shown by the homogeneity of the proverbs, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 15:19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 12:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", which form the conclusion of the first and second sections. We place together first in this new section, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 15:20-23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", in which (with the exception of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 15:25",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") the ישׂמח [maketh glad] of the first (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 10:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") is continued.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Proverbs 15:20",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 15:20",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "20 A wise son maketh a glad father,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "     And a fool of a man despiseth his mother.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Line first  equals  Proverbs 10:1. The gen. connection of כּסיל אדם (here and at Proverbs 21:20) is not superlative the most foolish of men, but like פּרא אדם, Genesis 16:12; the latter: a man of the wild ass kind; the former: a man of the fool kind, who is the exemplar of such a sort among men. Piety acting in willing subordination is wisdom, and the contrary exceeding folly.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Line first  equals  ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 10:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The gen. connection of כּסיל אדם (here and at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 21:20",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") is not superlative the most foolish of men, but like פּרא אדם, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 16:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; the latter: a man of the wild ass kind; the former: a man of the fool kind, who is the exemplar of such a sort among men. Piety acting in willing subordination is wisdom, and the contrary exceeding folly.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
